tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows mildly elevated creatinine, suggesting possible reduced kidney function, and a low fasting glucose, which may indicate hypoglycemia or recent fasting. HbA1c is at the upper end of normal, reflecting good long-term glycemic control. Other parameters are within normal limits. Clinical correlation and follow-up of renal function and glucose levels are recommended.
